org.sql: SELECT DISTINCT projects.id, projects.name FROM projects LEFT OUTER JOIN members ON projects.id = members.project_id AND members.user_id = 826 AND projects.active = True LEFT OUTER JOIN member_roles ON members.id = member_roles.member_id LEFT OUTER JOIN roles AS assigned_roles ON 1 = 1 AND projects.active = True AND (assigned_roles.id = member_roles.role_id OR projects.public = True AND assigned_roles.builtin = 1 AND member_roles.id IS NULL) WHERE projects.lft >= 1 AND projects.lft < 2 AND projects.id <> 347 AND assigned_roles.id IS NOT NULL ORDER BY projects.name ASC
